THE man who allegedly stabbed Brian Ubombo (27) to death appeared in the Mhala Magistrates Court in Thulamahashe near Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga, yesterday. The 29-year-old from Rolle Village was bust after his parents handed him over to the cops on Friday. READ: RAGE OVER KFC WEDDING! He faces a murder charge and wasn’t asked to plead. Ubombo was stabbed on Christmas Day and was rushed to hospital by his friends. The court heard that Ubombo was allegedly stabbed after he tried to separate people who were fighting at a local bar at Merry Pebble Stream. It was reported he was stabbed on the upper body and his friends rushed him to Mapulaneng Hospital, but he was certified dead on arrival. READ: PABALLO'S LOVER: MY WIFE DIDN'T KILL HER! Prosecutor Musa Makhubele asked that the case be postponed to next month after he agreed with the defence attorney, Peter Malibe. Magistrate Fortune Mhlaba postponed the case to Monday for a formal bail hearing. The accused will be in jail until his next court appearance.